\name{BioPlotBlocks-package}
\alias{BioPlotBlocks}
\alias{BioPlotBlocks-package}
\title{BioPlotBlocks: Faithful visual composition for R and ggplot2}
\description{
BioPlotBlocks provides a declarative ggplot2 module registry, typed R semantic
values, deterministic R code generation, supported-subset parsing, versioned
project persistence, controlled local execution, and a Shiny visual editor.
}
\details{
The initial package scope is R and ggplot2 only. Unsupported inner expressions
are retained as Raw R Expressions instead of being silently rewritten or lost.
}
\docType{package}
